<div class="recipe row">
  <div class="title col-md-12">
    <h2 id="ice-water-pickles">
      Marguerite's Ice Water Pickles</h2>
    <p>Makes 3 quarts</p>
  </div>

  <div class="image col-md-6">
    <img class="img-fluid" src="<%= image_path('ice_water_pickles.png') %>" />
  </div>

  <div class="instructions col-md-6">
    <h3>Ingredients</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>1 quart vinegar</li>
      <li>1 1/2 cup sugar</li>
      <li>1/2 cup pickling salt</li>
      <li>Mustard seed</li>
      <li>Cucumbers</li>
      <li>Yellow onion</li>
      <li>Celery</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Directions</h4>
    <p>Cut cucumbers lengthwise, thin strips (If seeds are very large, these aren’t so good). Cover with ice water 2 or 3 hours until real crisp (I use ice cubes, it is faster).</p>
    <p>Peel 2 slices onion in quart jar, pack pickles in, put celery stalks in center, add ½ tsp mustard seed.  Put little more onion on top.</p>
    <p>Cover with boiling solution of 1 quart vinegar, 1 ½ cup sugar and ½ cup salt</p>
    <p>(Maybe you will just want to make pints as it takes quite a few)</p>
  </div>
</div>

